 "**Analyzing Existentialism's Core**\n\nI'm currently breaking down the existentialist perspective, focusing on how individuals construct meaning in a meaningless universe. Sartre and Camus keep bubbling to the surface. I'm exploring the nuances of their philosophies.\n\n\n**Formulating Meaning Responses**\n\nI'm now streamlining the possible answers to \"What is the meaning of life?\" I've weighed the philosophical, biological, and pop-culture perspectives. Refining each response to its most concise form. The goal is a balanced response that doesn't ignore the diversity of thought. I've drafted a few options, settling on a final, nuanced answer.\n\n\n"
 "The meaning of life is subjective and depends on your perspective:\n\n1.  **Philosophical:** It is whatever purpose you choose to give it through your actions, relationships, and experiences.\n2.  **Biological:** To survive, adapt, and pass on genetic information to the next generation.\n3.  **Existential:** To create your own essence and values in an indifferent universe.\n4.  **Pop Culture:** According to Douglas Adams, it is **42**.\n\nUltimately, you are the author of your own meaning.")
